WEBVTT

00:02.333 --> 00:03.734
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

00:03.734 --> 00:06.677
COMING!

00:06.677 --> 00:09.640
[ SIGHS ] I FINALLY
 LEFT HER, GEORGE.

00:09.640 --> 00:11.142
SHE WAS SUFFOCATING ME.

00:11.142 --> 00:13.144
SHE KEPT ASKING ME,
 "WHERE AM I GOING?"

00:13.144 --> 00:14.415
"WHEN AM I COMING HOME?"

00:14.415 --> 00:17.548
HOW CAN YOU LIVE WITH A WOMAN
 THAT DOESN´T TRUST YOU?

00:17.548 --> 00:19.520
ANOTHER FIGHT
 WITH YOUR MOM?

00:19.520 --> 00:22.793
YEAH.
 A BIG ONE THIS TIME.

00:22.793 --> 00:25.496
SHE´S NOT IN THE BAG,
 IS SHE?

00:25.496 --> 00:27.358
NO, DUDE, THAT´S MY STUFF.

00:27.358 --> 00:29.300
I MOVED OUT OF
 MY FOLKS´ HOUSE.

00:29.300 --> 00:31.031
SO WHERE ARE YOU GONNA GO?

00:31.031 --> 00:32.762
WELL, REMEMBER
 THAT TIME YOU SAID

00:32.762 --> 00:36.137
I COULD STAY AT YOUR HOUSE
 WHENEVER I WANTED?

00:36.137 --> 00:38.169
MAN, THAT WAS
 IN THE SECOND GRADE!

00:38.169 --> 00:41.712
I WAS BEING NICE TO YOU BECAUSE
 YOU GAVE ME A VALENTINE.

00:41.712 --> 00:44.175
ANGIE, ERNIE GOT IN
 A FIGHT WITH HIS FOLKS,

00:44.175 --> 00:46.046
SO IS IT OKAY
 IF HE STAYS HERE?

00:46.046 --> 00:47.648
OF COURSE.
 ERNIE, WHAT HAPPENED?

00:47.648 --> 00:50.581
AH, MY MOM DOESN´T LIKE
 MY NEW GIRLFRIEND, LINDA.

00:50.581 --> 00:53.424
SHE THINKS LINDA´S USING ME
 BECAUSE SHE´S NOT WORKING,

00:53.424 --> 00:56.056
AND SHE HAS THREE KIDS
 FROM THREE DIFFERENT FATHERS,

00:56.056 --> 00:59.230
AND I MADE HER
 A COUPLE OF LOANS.

00:59.230 --> 01:02.363
HEY, MAN, IS THERE A SCAR
 WHERE YOUR KIDNEY SHOULD BE?

01:02.363 --> 01:04.694
AS LONG AS SHE
 MAKES YOU HAPPY, BRO.

01:04.694 --> 01:07.338
OH, SHE MAKES ME HAPPY.

01:07.338 --> 01:12.373
BELIEVE ME, SHE MAKES ME
 VERY, VERY HAPPY, HUH?

01:12.373 --> 01:14.445
YEOW! YEOW!

01:14.445 --> 01:17.708
OKAY, ERNIE.
 WE KNOW YOU GOT SOME.

01:17.708 --> 01:19.550
OH, NO, I DIDN´T,

01:19.550 --> 01:22.353
BUT SHE MAKES ME HAPPY.

01:22.353 --> 01:23.314
[ LAUGHS ]

01:30.761 --> 01:32.363
YOU WANT TO PLAY A GAME?

01:32.363 --> 01:35.396
I CAN´T RIGHT NOW. I GOT
 TO READ THIS THING FOR WORK.

01:38.429 --> 01:40.501
[ SLURPING ]

01:42.633 --> 01:46.677
MAN, YOU GUYS GOT
 THE BEST BOARD GAMES.

01:46.677 --> 01:47.778
SIX.

01:47.778 --> 01:49.240
THREE.

01:49.240 --> 01:50.181
TWO.

01:50.181 --> 01:53.384
FOUR. FOUR. FOUR. FOUR.

01:53.384 --> 01:56.517
FOUR. FOUR. FOUR. FOUR.

01:56.517 --> 01:58.149
DUDE!

02:01.722 --> 02:04.655
STOP THE DICE, MAN!

02:04.655 --> 02:06.527
I GOT TO READ
 THIS THING BY MONDAY.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.729
I GOT TO RECOMMEND A RETIREMENT
 PLAN FOR YOU GUYS.

02:08.729 --> 02:11.832
THIS COULD DETERMINE WHETHER
 YOU´RE PLAYING BINGO FOR FUN

02:11.832 --> 02:14.605
OR BINGO FOR SURVIVAL.

02:14.605 --> 02:15.866
HEY, I´M SORRY.

02:15.866 --> 02:19.370
LISTEN, I REALLY APPRECIATE
 YOU LETTING ME STAY HERE.

02:19.370 --> 02:20.671
I´LL JUST SAY
 GOOD NIGHT TO LINDA,

02:20.671 --> 02:22.513
THEN YOU WON´T EVEN
 KNOW I´M HERE.

02:25.316 --> 02:28.148
[ Deep voice ] HEY, BABY.

02:29.920 --> 02:32.283
IT´S SWEET DADDY.

02:34.725 --> 02:36.857
[ Normal voice ] ERNIE.

02:36.857 --> 02:38.259
IT´S ERNIE!

02:38.259 --> 02:39.730
I JUST, UH,

02:39.730 --> 02:44.895
I WANTED MY VOICE TO BE
 THE LAST ONE YOU HEAR TONIGHT.

02:44.895 --> 02:47.268
OH, YOU´RE GOING OUT?

02:47.268 --> 02:48.799
WELL, WHEN CAN I SEE YOU?

02:48.799 --> 02:50.541
OH, I DON´T KNOW.
 I´LL ASK.

02:50.541 --> 02:53.374
HEY, CAN LINDA AND HER KIDS
 COME OVER TOMORROW?

02:53.374 --> 02:54.745
YEAH. SURE.

02:54.745 --> 02:57.548
THOSE KIDS HAVE PROBABLY
 NEVER SEEN

02:57.548 --> 02:59.550
A HOUSE
 WITHOUT WHEELS BEFORE.

02:59.550 --> 03:03.254
HEY, BABY, I´M BACK.

03:03.254 --> 03:05.256
NO, ERNIE!

03:11.762 --> 03:13.764
DAD, ARE YOU BUSY?

03:13.764 --> 03:16.297
UM, YEAH, MAX.
 WHAT DO YOU WANT?

03:16.297 --> 03:18.469
UM, CAN YOU SIGN SOMETHING
 FOR SCHOOL?

03:18.469 --> 03:19.700
WE´RE GOING TO THE ZOO...

03:19.700 --> 03:21.802
UH, SCIENCE...

03:21.802 --> 03:23.904
SPACE PLACE.

03:23.904 --> 03:25.436
YEAH.

03:25.436 --> 03:27.808
SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

03:27.808 --> 03:29.380
WHAT SOUNDS LIKE FUN?

03:29.380 --> 03:33.584
HE´S GOING TO THE
 ZOO-SCIENCE-SPACE-THING PLACE.

03:33.584 --> 03:35.416
MAX, LET ME SEE THAT NOTE.

03:35.416 --> 03:36.517
DAD ALREADY SIGNED IT.

03:36.517 --> 03:37.718
GIVE IT TO ME.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.850
SHE´S UNDERMINING
 YOUR AUTHORITY!

03:44.855 --> 03:47.498
THIS IS FOR
 A PARENT-TEACHER CONFERENCE.

03:47.498 --> 03:49.560
HONEY, WHAT HAPPENED?

03:49.560 --> 03:51.302
THE TEACHER HATES ME.

03:51.302 --> 03:54.605
THE TEACHER CAN´T JUST
 HATE YOU, MAX. WHAT DID YOU DO?

03:54.605 --> 03:56.367
THERE WAS THIS STUPID TEST.

03:56.367 --> 04:00.311
I DIDN´T FEEL LIKE TAKING IT,
 SO I DREW A PICTURE.

04:00.311 --> 04:02.413
OF...?

04:02.413 --> 04:03.844
MY TEACHER...

04:05.546 --> 04:08.419
TAKING A TEST...

04:08.419 --> 04:10.351
IN HELL.

04:10.351 --> 04:12.653
[ LAUGHS ]

04:12.653 --> 04:15.356
SON, THAT´S WRONG.

04:15.356 --> 04:18.257
MAX, WHY DIDN´T YOU
 TAKE THE TEST?

04:18.257 --> 04:19.690
I DON´T KNOW!

04:21.362 --> 04:24.495
GEORGE, OUR CHILD
 JUST WALKED AWAY FROM US.

04:24.495 --> 04:27.037
THE GOOD ONE.

04:27.037 --> 04:28.899
ANGIE, I´VE GOT
 ALL THIS WORK TO DO.

04:28.899 --> 04:30.371
CAN YOU DEAL WITH IT?

04:30.371 --> 04:32.873
NO! MAX HAS NEVER BEEN
 IN TROUBLE AT SCHOOL BEFORE.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.775
WE´RE BOTH GOING
 TO THAT MEETING.

04:34.775 --> 04:37.308
CAN´T WE DO IT ON THE PHONE?

04:37.308 --> 04:40.050
MY MOM NEVER
 WENT TO MY SCHOOL.

04:40.050 --> 04:43.954
SHE ONLY WENT TO MY GRADUATION
 TO HECKLE ME.

04:43.954 --> 04:48.419
"OH, LOOK AT HIM,
 MR. OH-YOU-THINK-YOU´RE-ALL-BAD.

04:48.419 --> 04:52.963
MR. HIGH-SCHOOL-DIPLOMA.
 MR. I-KNOW-WHERE-AFRICA-IS."

04:54.925 --> 04:56.727
WHAT?

04:56.727 --> 04:58.869
YOU ARE SO DAMAGED.

05:00.671 --> 05:01.902
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

05:01.902 --> 05:04.375
WE BOTH GOT TO TALK
 TO THAT TEACHER.

05:04.375 --> 05:06.006
ALL RIGHT.

05:06.006 --> 05:08.779
HEY, BUT LISTEN -- YOU KNOW
 HOW SOMETIMES AT NIGHT

05:08.779 --> 05:10.711
YOU CALL ME "SWEET DADDY"?

05:12.483 --> 05:15.085
DON´T DO THAT ANYMORE.

05:15.085 --> 05:17.718
[ INTRO TO WAR´S "LOW RIDER"
 PLAYS ]

05:28.559 --> 05:30.601
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS ♫

05:30.601 --> 05:33.364
♫ KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

05:34.865 --> 05:39.710
♫ THE LOW RIDER
 IS A LITTLE HIGHER ♫

06:04.565 --> 06:06.697
"ALL ABOUT ME."

06:06.697 --> 06:07.968
OH, GEORGE.

06:07.968 --> 06:10.641
LOOK AT THESE
 LITTLE AUTOBIOGRAPHIES.

06:10.641 --> 06:13.904
"I´M BRANDY.
 I LOVE BRITNEY SPEARS,

06:13.904 --> 06:17.508
"AND I DON´T HAVE A DAD.

06:17.508 --> 06:19.510
"BUT THAT´S OKAY

06:19.510 --> 06:21.852
"BECAUSE MY MOM
 SAYS I´M PRETTY,

06:21.852 --> 06:25.816
AND THE WORLD LOVES
 A PRETTY GIRL."

06:25.816 --> 06:28.689
THERE´S A FUTURE STRIPPER.

06:28.689 --> 06:32.863
MR. AND MRS. LOPEZ,
 THANK YOU FOR COMING DOWN.

06:32.863 --> 06:37.868
LET ME START BY SAYING MAX
 IS A JOY TO HAVE IN CLASS.

06:37.868 --> 06:39.570
HE´S A JOY AT HOME.

06:39.570 --> 06:41.602
AND HE LIKES YOU, TOO.

06:41.602 --> 06:44.475
HE DRAWS ALL HIS
 FAVORITE PEOPLE IN HELL.

06:46.076 --> 06:47.638
GOOD.

06:47.638 --> 06:50.881
UM, LOOK, MAX IS HAVING
 REAL PROBLEMS WITH HIS READING.

06:50.881 --> 06:53.113
HAVE YOU SEEN HIS CENTIPEDE?

06:57.818 --> 07:00.551
I DON´T KNOW WHAT THAT´S
 GOT TO DO WITH READING,

07:00.551 --> 07:02.923
BUT IN OUR HOUSE,
 WE CALL IT A "WEENIS."

07:02.923 --> 07:04.154
UH, NO.

07:04.154 --> 07:06.657
JUST LOOK UP
 AT THE WALL HERE.

07:06.657 --> 07:09.500
YOU SEE, EACH TIME
 A STUDENT FINISHES A BOOK,

07:09.500 --> 07:11.532
WE ADD A SEGMENT
 TO THEIR CENTIPEDE.

07:11.532 --> 07:12.763
FOR EXAMPLE, DAKOTA HERE

07:12.763 --> 07:15.065
HAS ALREADY READ
 20 BOOKS THIS YEAR.

07:15.065 --> 07:16.467
WHERE´S MAX´S?

07:16.467 --> 07:18.769
IT´S JUST THAT HEAD
 UP THERE.

07:20.611 --> 07:23.974
MISS WILDER, WHAT EXACTLY
 IS THE PROBLEM?

07:23.974 --> 07:25.716
WELL, WE´VE TESTED MAX,

07:25.716 --> 07:29.149
AND IT SEEMS HE HAS
 A LEARNING DISABILITY.

07:29.149 --> 07:31.021
WE THINK HE´S DYSLEXIC.

07:31.021 --> 07:32.583
WHAT? THAT CAN´T BE RIGHT.

07:32.583 --> 07:34.555
I KNOW HE´S NOT
 THE BEST STUDENT,

07:34.555 --> 07:35.856
BUT HE´S A REALLY SMART BOY.

07:35.856 --> 07:38.489
NO, IT HAS NOTHING TO DO
 WITH INTELLIGENCE.

07:38.489 --> 07:41.532
IT HAS TO DO WITH THE WAY
 HE PROCESSES LANGUAGE.

07:41.532 --> 07:43.664
SOMETIMES HIS BRAIN
 REVERSES LETTERS,

07:43.664 --> 07:45.596
WHICH MAKES IT
 HARDER FOR HIM

07:45.596 --> 07:47.538
TO COMPREHEND
 WHAT HE´S READING.

07:47.538 --> 07:49.469
WELL, WHAT CAN WE DO
 TO HELP HIM?

07:49.469 --> 07:52.503
WELL, I THINK MAX SHOULD BEGIN
 SPECIAL-EDUCATION CLASSES.

07:52.503 --> 07:55.546
YOU WANT TO PUT MY SON IN
 SPECIAL ED? NO. NO WAY.

07:55.546 --> 07:58.048
BUT, GEORGE, IF HE
 NEEDS THE CLASSES --

07:58.048 --> 07:59.550
NO, ANGIE!

07:59.550 --> 08:01.211
YOU´RE NOT GONNA
 PUT MY KID IN SPECIAL ED

08:01.211 --> 08:03.614
SO ALL THE OTHER KIDS
 CAN MAKE FUN OF HIM!
 GEORGE!

08:03.614 --> 08:06.817
MR. LOPEZ, IF HE DOESN´T
 GET THE TOOLS HE NEEDS TO READ,

08:06.817 --> 08:08.258
HE COULD BE HELD BACK.

08:08.258 --> 08:10.861
DOES EVERY KID IN THIS CLASS
 READ THE WAY THEY SHOULD?

08:10.861 --> 08:12.693
HE´S A BOY.
 HE´LL GROW OUT OF IT.

08:12.693 --> 08:15.225
I APPRECIATE YOUR CONCERN,
 BUT THIS IS A SCHOOL,

08:15.225 --> 08:17.568
AND YOU´RE A TEACHER,
 SO WHY DON´T YOU TEACH HIM?

08:17.568 --> 08:19.870
WELL, WHY DON´T I LET
 YOU TWO DISCUSS THIS?

08:19.870 --> 08:23.574
WE DON´T NEED TO DISCUSS IT,
 ´CAUSE WE´RE LOPEZES.

08:23.574 --> 08:25.706
AND WE DON´T ASK FOR HELP,
 AND WE DON´T GET HELP.

08:25.706 --> 08:29.680
AND EVEN WHEN WE GET HELP,
 WE DON´T TAKE IT, BECAUSE
 WE DON´T DESERVE IT.

08:32.783 --> 08:34.745
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

08:34.745 --> 08:39.119
I DON´T KNOW, BUT I DON´T
 NEED YOUR HELP!

08:39.119 --> 08:41.150
I´M SORRY.

08:48.258 --> 08:49.600
ERNIE, WHAT´S GOING ON?

08:49.600 --> 08:50.861
I´M MAKING LUNCH
 FOR THE KIDS.

08:50.861 --> 08:53.063
THEN I GOT TO TAKE BRANDON
 TO SOCCER PRACTICE

08:53.063 --> 08:54.134
AND CONNIE TO BALLET.

08:54.134 --> 08:55.666
WELL, WHERE´S THEIR MOTHER?

08:55.666 --> 08:57.237
OH, IT´S OUR
 3-WEEK ANNIVERSARY.

08:57.237 --> 08:58.609
SHE WANTED TO CELEBRATE,

08:58.609 --> 09:00.711
SO SHE WENT TO A SPA
 UP IN OJAI.

09:05.916 --> 09:09.620
HEY, MAN, GO LIKE THIS.

09:09.620 --> 09:11.752
OH, THIS IS CLEM, JR.

09:11.752 --> 09:16.086
HEY, THING ONE, THING TWO,
 TAKE IT OUTSIDE.

09:16.086 --> 09:17.588
WE CAN´T GO OUT.

09:17.588 --> 09:19.930
THE YARD LADY´S WORKING WITH
 THAT DUMB KID.

09:19.930 --> 09:21.792
WHAT THE HELL?

09:21.792 --> 09:24.795
HEY, NOT IN FRONT
 OF CLEM JR.!

09:24.795 --> 09:28.839
OKAY, WHAT LETTER
 COMES NEXT?

09:28.839 --> 09:30.100
"G"?

09:30.100 --> 09:31.171
TRY AGAIN, HONEY.

09:31.171 --> 09:32.673
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

09:32.673 --> 09:34.705
IT´S JUST AN EXERCISE.
 I HOLD UP A LETTER,

09:34.705 --> 09:36.907
AND YOU TELL ME THE LETTER
 THAT COMES AFTER IT.

09:36.907 --> 09:38.108
ANYBODY CAN DO THAT.

09:38.108 --> 09:39.710
BUT YOU HAVE TO DO IT

09:39.710 --> 09:42.082
WITHOUT SINGING
 THE ALPHABET SONG.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.785
TRY IT.

09:47.718 --> 09:50.661
OH, SURE, "Q."
 IT´S THE HARDEST ONE!

09:50.661 --> 09:53.664
GEORGE, IT´S SUPPOSED
 TO BE RANDOM.

09:53.664 --> 09:56.667
THEN YOU TRY IT.
 OKAY.

09:58.769 --> 09:59.770
"S."

09:59.770 --> 10:00.771
"N."

10:00.771 --> 10:01.301
"H."

10:01.301 --> 10:02.633
"V."

10:03.674 --> 10:06.737
YOU KNOW WHAT?
 THAT´S NOT A TURN-ON.

10:06.737 --> 10:09.810
COME ON, KIDS, WE GOT
 TO GET MOVING.

10:09.810 --> 10:13.814
HEY, I DON´T WANT TO BE LATE
 FOR MY "MOMMY AND ME" CLASS.

10:13.814 --> 10:15.115
BYE, GUYS!

10:15.115 --> 10:17.247
SEE YOU, "SLOW-PEZ."

10:19.219 --> 10:21.021
YOU HEAR THAT KID?

10:21.021 --> 10:23.754
THAT´S WHAT IT WOULD BE LIKE
 IF WE SEND HIM TO SPECIAL ED.

10:23.754 --> 10:26.727
SPECIAL ED? I DON´T WANT
 TO BE IN SPECIAL ED.

10:26.727 --> 10:28.829
IS THAT WHY
 YOU´RE DOING THIS?

10:28.829 --> 10:30.831
George:
 TELL THE TRUTH, MAX.

10:30.831 --> 10:33.403
HAVE YOU BEEN DOING
 YOUR BEST AT SCHOOL?

10:33.403 --> 10:35.035
NO, I GUESS NOT.

10:35.035 --> 10:37.838
PROMISE YOU´LL DO BETTER?
 YOU´LL READ MORE?

10:37.838 --> 10:39.239
YES.

10:39.239 --> 10:41.341
OKAY, THEN NO
 SPECIAL ED FOR YOU.

10:41.341 --> 10:44.074
THANKS, DAD. I PROMISE
 I´LL WORK REALLY HARD.

10:46.947 --> 10:47.978
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

10:47.978 --> 10:49.249
WHAT WAS THAT?

10:49.249 --> 10:52.322
THAT WAS ME MAKING A DECISION
 WITHOUT CONSULTING YOU FIRST,

10:52.322 --> 10:55.425
AND NOW THIS IS THE FIGHT
 ABOUT THAT.

10:55.425 --> 10:57.988
GEORGE, I DON´T WANT
 TO FIGHT ABOUT THIS.

10:57.988 --> 10:59.960
I WANT TO HELP MAX.

10:59.960 --> 11:02.993
WE DON´T EVEN KNOW IF
 HE´S GOT DYSLEXIA. WHY?
 BECAUSE ONE TEACHER SAID SO?

11:02.993 --> 11:06.296
NO. I´VE BEEN READING ABOUT IT.
 HE´S GOT ALL THE SIGNS.

11:06.296 --> 11:07.838
NOT ONLY THAT --

11:07.838 --> 11:10.270
GEORGE, IT CAN BE GENETIC.

11:10.270 --> 11:12.102
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

11:12.102 --> 11:14.004
I THINK YOU HAVE IT, TOO.

11:14.004 --> 11:15.105
OH, GREAT.

11:15.105 --> 11:18.008
YOU´RE SAYING THAT
 I PASSED IT ON TO HIM?

11:18.008 --> 11:19.780
I DON´T THINK SO, ANGIE.

11:19.780 --> 11:22.813
THERE´S NOTHING WRONG
 WITH MY CENTIPEDE.

11:24.715 --> 11:28.058
GEORGE, THIS IS NOTHING
 TO BE ASHAMED OF.

11:28.058 --> 11:30.791
SOME OF THE MOST
 PROMINENT PEOPLE IN HISTORY

11:30.791 --> 11:31.762
HAVE BEEN DYSLEXIC.

11:31.762 --> 11:33.764
EINSTEIN, da VINCI,

11:33.764 --> 11:35.365
CHURCHILL, CHER...

11:35.365 --> 11:38.899
CHURCHILL.

11:38.899 --> 11:41.972
COME ON! IF I HAD IT, DON´T
 YOU THINK I´D KNOW BY NOW?!

11:41.972 --> 11:44.775
NOT NECESSARILY. YOU WERE
 ON THE LINE FOR 15 YEARS.

11:44.775 --> 11:46.076
YOU DIDN´T HAVE TO READ.

11:46.076 --> 11:48.839
ALL THESE BOOKS TALK ABOUT
 HOW PEOPLE WITH DYSLEXIA

11:48.839 --> 11:50.240
FIND WAYS
 TO GET OUT OF READING.

11:50.240 --> 11:52.282
WHERE DOES IT SAY THAT?
 RIGHT HERE.

11:52.282 --> 11:54.014
READ IT TO ME.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.019
GEORGE, YOU´RE DOING IT.

11:59.019 --> 12:01.221
I CAN´T BE DOING ANYTHING,
 BECAUSE I DON´T HAVE ANYTHING.

12:01.221 --> 12:03.854
AND I NEVER
 GAVE MAX ANYTHING...

12:03.854 --> 12:06.056
EXCEPT A GREAT HEAD
 OF HAIR.

12:07.457 --> 12:09.099
AND SALMONELLA,

12:09.099 --> 12:13.103
THAT ONE TIME I TRIED TO MAKE
 MY OWN CHICKEN FINGERS.

12:19.840 --> 12:21.341
HEY, GEORGE.
 YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

12:21.341 --> 12:23.413
YEAH, LISTEN, I HAVEN´T
 FINISHED READING THIS YET,

12:23.413 --> 12:26.276
SO GIVE ME THE HEADS-UP IF
 YOU SEE THE POWERS BROTHERS.

12:26.276 --> 12:27.747
NO PROBLEM.

12:29.419 --> 12:32.482
WELL, GEORGE, HAVE YOU
 ANALYZED THE REPORT?

12:32.482 --> 12:34.985
[ NO AUDIO ]

12:39.429 --> 12:42.062
YEAH, SURE. YOU KNOW, I JUST
 NEED TO MAKE SOME COPIES.

12:42.062 --> 12:44.234
HELL, GEORGE, WE DON´T
 NEED TO READ ANYTHING.

12:44.234 --> 12:46.066
WE KNOW WHICH PLAN
 WE THINK IS BEST.

12:46.066 --> 12:47.437
BUT WHAT DO YOU RECOMMEND?

12:47.437 --> 12:49.369
WELL, YOU KNOW,

12:49.369 --> 12:52.202
I´VE BEEN CONSIDERING
 THE COLOMBIA 401(k)...

12:53.503 --> 12:56.376
BUT I´M ALSO INTERESTED
 IN THE JANUS PENSION...

12:57.948 --> 13:00.811
AND THEN THERE´S
 THE GRUBSTICK PLAN...

13:01.952 --> 13:04.815
WHICH IS THE ONE
 THAT I RECOMMEND 100%.

13:04.815 --> 13:06.786
WOW, THAT WOULD
 SAVE US A BUNDLE.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.859
WHO´D HAVE THOUGHT
 YOU´D BE AGAINST

13:08.859 --> 13:11.461
PAYING FOR NURSING HOMES?

13:11.461 --> 13:15.525
I GUESS IF THEY´RE MAD AT YOU,
 THEY WON´T BE MAD FOR LONG!

13:15.525 --> 13:17.898
OH, NO, NO, NO.
 WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

13:17.898 --> 13:20.530
WE CAN´T DO AWAY
 WITH NURSING HOMES.

13:20.530 --> 13:22.873
MY MOM DIDN´T SMOKE
 FOR 40 YEARS

13:22.873 --> 13:24.804
TO DIE ALONE IN MY ATTIC.

13:24.804 --> 13:26.276
WHAT ARE YOU
 TALKING ABOUT?

13:26.276 --> 13:28.208
YOU KNOW, I CAN´T
 RECOMMEND ANYTHING

13:28.208 --> 13:30.810
BECAUSE I DIDN´T FINISH
 READING THE PROPOSAL.

13:30.810 --> 13:32.212
OH, DAMN IT, GEORGE.

13:32.212 --> 13:35.916
THIS JOB ISN´T ONLY
 RUNNING THE PLANT FLOOR.

13:35.916 --> 13:38.088
